HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 394
BY REPRESENTATIVE MENA
A RESOLUTION
To express the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death of Dr. L'Isaa
LaChandra Gates.
WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the passing, on May 25, 2026,
of Dr. L'Isaa LaChandra Gates; and
WHEREAS, L'Isaa LaChandra Gates was born on May 3, 1982, to Jeffery Gates and
CaSandra Cooper-Gates in New Orleans, Louisiana; she was educated in the Orleans Parish
Public School System and graduated from Benjamin Franklin Senior High School in 1999;
and
WHEREAS, Dr. Gates attended Xavier University of Louisiana, where she received
a bachelor of science degree in biology/pre-medicine and graduated magna cum laude with
honors in biology and chemistry in 2003; she attended Louisiana State University Health
Sciences Center in New Orleans and graduated with a doctor of medicine degree in 2007;
and
WHEREAS, Dr. Gates completed a residency training program in pediatrics with the
LSU School of Medicine and began a practice in pediatrics with Westside Clinics, AMC,
where she eventually became a partner; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Gates's practice was merged into Ochsner for Children-Westside
Pediatrics, where she served as a senior attending physician; at the time of her passing, she
was scheduled to serve as an assistant professor of pediatrics at the developing Xavier
Ochsner College of Medicine; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Gates was an alumna of the Rosenblum Healthcare Institute and
Committee for a Better New Orleans/Bryan Bell Metropolitan Leadership Forum; she was
a member of the Delgado Community College Care & Development of Young Children
Board of Advisors, where she provided her keen expertise in child care and commitment to
quality and affordable healthcare; and
