WHEREAS, Dr. Gates was licensed by the Louisiana State Board of Medical
Examiners and the Louisiana Department of Education; she was a member of Alpha Omega
Alpha Medical, Beta Beta Beta Biological, Phi Lambda Upsilon Chemical, Alpha Epsilon
Delta Premedical, Delta Omega Public Health, and Omicron Delta Kappa Leadership and
Phi Beta Kappa, Phi Theta Kappa, Alpha Kappa Mu, Mortar Board, and Phi Sigma Theta
Scholastic Honor Societies; she was also a member of the American Medical Association
and was a Fellow of the American Academy of Pediatrics; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Gates was a positive and visible role model in her community, and
she participated in the American Medical Association Doctors Back to School (STEM)
program and was a Junior Achievement Volunteer; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Gates championed the causes of numerous organizations, including
the American Cancer Society, Breast Cancer Research Foundation, Susan G. Komen
Foundation, Muscular Dystrophy Association, Multiple Sclerosis Foundation, and March of
Dimes; she gave selflessly to local initiatives that directly impacted women, minorities, and
the community; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Gates was recognized for her efforts in philanthropy and received
awards from East Baton Rouge Parish, Jefferson Parish, the mayor of New Orleans, the New
Orleans City Council, the Legislature of Louisiana, the president, and congress; she was
recognized as Data News Weekly's 2013 Trailblazer, New Orleans Magazine's Top Female
Achiever, and Gambit Weekly's 40 Under 40; New Orleans City Business Magazine listed
her among its Ones to Watch and Women of the Year and lauded her as a Healthcare Hero;
and
WHEREAS, Dr. Gates was a member of Second Mount Everest Baptist Church,
where she served in the choir, administrative office staff, Sunday school, and prayer
ministry; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Gates is survived by her loving parents, Jeffery Gates and CaSandra
Cooper-Gates; grandmothers, Annie Dupree Cooper and Audrey Smith Gates; fiancé,
Dr. Derek Bardell; great-aunts, Fran Dupree and Beverly Dupree; great-uncle and godfather,
Isaac Dupree; godmother, Maxine Buckles; uncle, Lawrence Gates; "sister" and best friend,
Ebony Broussard; "big sister", Wendy Lewis; godchild, Tai Linton; "bonus aunt", Brenda
Wilson; and a host of cousins, extended relatives, and friends; she will be deeply missed, but
